message: Access to the dashboard is role-based. (Role-based access controls maintains that only pre-allocated roles having login credentials created for them can access the platform)
The acronyms used in the DSS and their full forms are listed below

Administrators - officials from Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs (MoHUA) & National Institute of Urban Affairs ( NIUA), a functional mission within it is NUDM ( National Urban Digital Mission ). Roles such as Director & Joint Secretaries of the above institutions are administrators.
API authentication while integration with the dashboard is maintained

The Dashboard was built with the purpose of ensuring data transparency, providing access to data, ensuring accountability, and assisting in data-driven decision-making. It also helps users understand the nature of information on the dashboard and its governance.
The dashboard receives aggregated data from the State . There is no visibility on who’s data it is & what the details of the data are, as all datasets are in the numerical form.

Data from the States is transmitted through secure APIs (every State Instance has to implement an adaptor service that would collate/aggregate the data at each functional service level and push the data to the National Dashboard elastic search through ingest service. National Dashboard picks up these data from the National Dashboard Elastic Search to show KPIs, tables, and graphs as visualisation)
Download the dataset for further study/policy-making purposes/ driving performance incentives any other purposes

The DIGIT National Urban Dashboard offers users a consolidated Decision Support System (DSS) tool with rich and interactive dashboards that provide a complete visualisation of the key metrics. It simplifies the data into more manageable chunks of visual information, that allow users to see areas of efficiency as well as areas of improvement.

Data in this dashboard is aggregated information from urban development services provided by States. This aggregated information contains no personally identifiable information. The data is sent to show the performance of the State as per variables set on the dashboard.
The data is stored at a central instance - an infrastructure that is owned by the MoHUA or NIUA.

The citizens share data while utilizing services provided by their respective urban local bodies. These datasets are collected by the State. MoUs are signed with the users and the States for sharing data on this dashboard. These states have either adopted DIGIT as a base for their urban service delivery or have a platform similar to that of DIGIT or have created their own digital way to provide information to this dashboard.

To share any individual cards such as overview or tables or charts, click on the kebab menu icon (three vertical dots) on the top right corner of each individual card. From the drop down click on the email or WhatsApp icon to share them as per your requirement
Share the data & analytics on the dashboard through WhatsApp or e-mail

The State aggregates the data and removes the personal identifying information from it for the purpose of sharing with the dashboard. The States use secure APIs for sharing such data. The States are to solely share information related to the performance/result of the urban local bodies on delivery of urban development services, in an aggregated form.

States - States whose data is presented on this dashboard are those that have adopted UPYOG, DIGIT, or platforms similar to these and that have signed an MoU with NUDM to be a part of this dashboard. The term includes departments in the State governments that manage the urban development / Urban local bodies (ULB) related works. The term also includes Union Territories and such departments in a Union Territory.

Urban development services - Urban development services include works in property tax collection, water & sewerage, trade license, birth & death, public grievance & redressal, fire NOC, miscellaneous payments (mCollect), and online building plan approval systems
Users- Currently, users of the dashboard are officials from the Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs (MoHUA) and/or personnel of the National Institute of Urban Affairs ( NIUA)

The values of each metric corresponding to the same time period for last year is denoted below each metric with an upward or downward arrow with a text X % than LY (Last Year). A positive change with respect to last year is indicated as an upward green arrow. A negative change is marked with a red downward arrow.
The definitions for various KPIs can be viewed by hovering over each KPI with the mouse pointer.
To view the data for any particular ULBs, repeat the same action for the filter box named ‘ULB’.

What data is to be shared is pre-determined by fixed metrics. Examples of these metrics are - total collections of property tax on a specific period for a state, total applications, or the total number of complaints received.
To download/share any individual cards such as overview or tables or charts, click on the kebab menu icon (three vertical dots) on the top right corner of each individual card.
The National Urban Dashboard enables users to:
Total property tax collected  / Total number of properties paid
Sum of all non tax revenue collections such as ( Trade licenses , Building plan approval , miscellaneous receipts , etc..)
The total number of Bills generated for the selected date range. Expense, Contractor and Supplier Bill
Total number of vouchers in the system. Includes all types of vouchers.
Sum of all the Bills (Bill Amount)
Total number of bill where status is Payment Done
Sum of amount of Payments made against Bills
Total number of receipt vouchers in the system. i.e count of voucher where type is Receipt
Sum of amount of all the receipt vouchers
Count of vendors in system from master (Contractor/Supplier)
Count of total Bank account in the system from Masters
Total # of properties registered on the system
# of properties for which assessments were generated
Today's collections from applying and renewing a trade license
Sum of target revenue for trade license set by the state/ULB
Total # of trade licenses issued by the concerned authority
Total # of complaints successfully resolved by the concerned authorities.
Total # of citizens registered on the system
